作的剪辑以 DMX 的“Party Up (Up In Here)”为背景，充满了高速追逐、枪支和劫车，还有大量的俏皮话和一个疯狂的小丑——这一切都是你对真人版改编电影所期待的一切。顶级特许经营权。</p><p>两分钟的预告片以主演安东尼·麦凯（ <em>《猎鹰》和《冬兵》</em> ）开始，为主角约翰·多伊定下了基调。 “20 年前，世界一团糟，”他解释道。 “城市筑起了围墙来保护自己，并将罪犯赶出去，这样他们就可以为剩下的东西而战。但也有像我这样卑微的混蛋，把货物从一个有城墙的城市运送到另一个城市。这就是汽车和枪支发挥作用的地方。”皮科克将这个系列描述为“高辛烷值的动作喜剧”，似乎有一种自我意识的基调，喜欢游戏的奢华，并会向观众眨眼（隐喻或其他方式）。想想<em>疯狂麦克斯</em>后世界末日荒原中的<em>死侍</em>式幽默。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="a9e217981709482799785e8e17f76877"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5QNZ44zKzjo" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p>除了麦基之外，该剧的主演斯蒂芬妮·贝翠丝（ <em>《布鲁克林九九》</em> ）饰演一名劫车歹徒，她在枪口的威胁下搭上了麦基的母鹿的便车。我们还可以看到内夫·坎贝尔饰演的乌鸦，他向多伊承诺送包裹会得到丰厚的奖励，托马斯·哈登·<em>丘奇</em>（《杯酒人生》）饰演斯通特工，摔跤手萨摩亚·乔（表演动作）和威尔·阿奈特（配音）饰演杀手小丑甜甜。齿。该系列由迈克尔·乔纳森·史密斯编写和开发。</p><p> <em>《扭​​曲金属》</em>将包括十集半小时的剧集。该剧于 7 月 27 日首播，在 Peacock 独家播出。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/twisted-metal-trailer-basks-in-post-apocalyptic-extravagance-211534351.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twisted-metal-trailer-basks-in-post-apocalyptic-extravagance-211534351.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9867fbed-09d6-4e78-8144-02f92698ef55</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jul 2023 21:15:34 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689023020</ingested><modified> 2023-07-10T21:03:45+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Celebrities]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/a30c6a60-1f62-11ee-9277-ea1cd7ea14be" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/a30c6a60-1f62-11ee-9277-ea1cd7ea14be" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Peacock]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Anthony Mackie as John Doe in the trailer for Peacock’s ‘Twisted Metal’ series. He sits in the driver’s seat of a car, looking outward with a wry grin.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[‘Twisted Metal’]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[People who don't use TikTok think it's a national security threat]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/can-tiktok-convince-the-us-its-not-a-national-security-threat-173030115.html">将 TikTok 视为国家安全威胁的</a>持续压力似乎正在发挥作用，尽管只是对某些人有效。皮尤研究中心的一项调查<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2023/07/10/majority-of-americans-say-tiktok-is-a-threat-to-national-security/">显示</a>，59% 的美国成年人将 TikTok 视为一种危险，但这种看法因人是否使用该服务而异。只有 9% 的 TikTok 用户将社交网络视为主要威胁，而 36% 的非用户也有同样的感觉。总而言之，42% 的用户认为该服务存在任何风险，而 65% 的外来者则对此感到担忧。</p><p>如果您听说年龄在人们对 TikTok 的认知中起着重要作用，您不会感到惊讶。在 30 岁以下的用户中，只有 49% 的人将 TikTok 视为威胁（只有 13% 的人将其视为主要威胁），但随着年龄的增长，这一数字会更高。 65 岁以上的人中，约 65% 对 TikTok 感到紧张，其中 46% 的人将其视为严重威胁。政治也是一个因素。高达 76% 的保守派人士对此表示担忧，而 49% 的自由派人士也有同样的看法。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>皮尤补充道，大约 64% 的美国成年人至少在某种程度上担心 TikTok 的数据处理做法。同样，这些数字会根据年龄而变化。 30 岁以下的人中只有 54% 有这种感觉，而 65 岁以上的人中这一比例为 75%。</p><p>这项研究是在蒙大拿州颁布<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/montanas-governor-signs-bill-banning-tiktok-225326086.html">禁止该州 TikTok 的法律</a>之际进行的，距离美国两大党政客<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senator-michael-bennet-tiktok-apple-google-ban-005604950.html">呼吁全国禁止</a>TikTok 已经很久了。该平台已在<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tiktok-us-government-ban-devices-omnibus-bill-funding-nasa-234803320.html">大多数联邦设备</a>上被禁止。推理常常是相似的。官员们担心，TikTok 的母公司字节跳动可能会将美国用户的数据提供给中国政府，或影响算法来传播亲中国的宣传。</p><p> TikTok <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tiktok-ceo-to-congress-bytedance-is-not-an-agent-of-china-173741845.html">一再否认</a>中国政府的影响力，并采取了一系列措施安抚美国政界人士。它<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tiktok-user-data-us-200500287.html">在国内存储美国数据</a>，提供代码透明度，并<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/bytedance-tiktok-employees-us-user-data-journalists-210339650.html">解雇不当访问敏感数据的员工</a>。然而，这些措施并没有起到太大的安抚政府代表的作用——皮尤研究中心的数据表明公众也同样持谨慎态度。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/people-who-dont-use-tiktok-think-its-a-national-security-threat-203921153.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/people-who-dont-use-tiktok-think-its-a-national-security-threat-203921153.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ff9bc104-1340-4a60-b62f-56b36b63e4af</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jul 2023 20:39:21 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689021563</ingested><modified> 2023-07-10T20:39:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="5504" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/8c382f00-f504-11ed-bc3d-ba68e53eb712" width="8256"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="5504" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/8c382f00-f504-11ed-bc3d-ba68e53eb712" width="8256"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The TikTok logo is seen on a mobile phone screen in this photo illustration on 23 March, 2023 in Warsaw, Poland. (Photo by Jaap Arriens/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[TikTok Faces Ban As CEO Testifies Before US Congress]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sega of America workers overwhelmingly vote to unionize]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/sega/"><ins>美国世嘉</ins></a>公司的工人投票<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sega-of-america-workers-are-forming-a-union-184043887.html"><ins>决定成立工会</ins></a>。在国家劳工关系委员会举行的工会代表选举中，工人们以 91 比 26 的投票结果支持他们的单位，即改善世嘉联盟雇员协会 (AEGIS-CWA)。十九张选票受到质疑，三张无效。结果，该组织现已与<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/cwa/"><ins>美国通信工人协会</ins></a>正式组织起来。</p><p>该部门由公司各个部门的 200 多名员工组成，包括品牌营销、游戏即服务、本地化、营销服务、产品开发、销售和质量保证团队。虽然这<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vodeo-games-shutting-down-213519398.html"><ins>不是</ins></a>北美<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/raven-software-activision-blizzard-union-game-workers-alliance-195516977.html"><ins>第一个游戏工会</ins></a>，但工人表示，它是“整个游戏行业最大的有组织工人的多部门工会”。然而，ZeniMax Workers United/CWA 在 ZeniMax Studios 拥有<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-union-zenimax-vote-recognize-190529301.html"><ins>约 300 名质量保证人员</ins></a>。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="7429fc4d2daa445b8904911eb61403f7"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">我们赢了！<br><br>我们刚刚以 91 比 26 赢得了工会选举。<br><br>我们的工会拥有 200 多名会员，目前是整个游戏行业最大的、由有组织的工人组成的多部门工会。<br><br>非常高兴能够庆祝这一胜利，并与<a href="https://twitter.com/SEGA?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@SEGA</a>一起走向谈判桌，继续建设这家我们热爱的公司！ <a href="https://t.co/2iy6loAruf">pic.twitter.com/2iy6loAruf</a></p> — AEGIS-CWA 💙 #UnionizeSEGA (@takesAEGIS) <a href="https://twitter.com/takesAEGIS/status/1678481056520101889?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 7 月 10 日</a></blockquote></div><p>AEGIS-CWA 计划推动提高基本工资和福利、增加员工以“消除过度工作模式”以及更加平衡的工作量。工人们还寻求远程工作选择、每个角色的明确职责等等。</p><p>世嘉拒绝自愿承认该工会。 QA 测试员兼 AEGIS-CWA 成员 Winry Ramsey 此前曾表示，管理层<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/sega-of-america-staff-say-their-employer-is-undermining-their-unionization-drive"><ins>决定</ins></a>“转而与已知的工会破坏者接触，试图传播错误信息、恐惧和分裂”。世嘉现在必须与 AEGIS-CWA 就工会合同达成一致。</p><p> &quot;We are overjoyed to celebrate our union election win as members of AEGIS-CWA. From the start of this campaign, it has been clear that we all care deeply about our work at Sega,&quot; Sega translator and AEGIS-CWA member Ángel Gómez said in a statement. &quot;Now, through our union, we&#39;ll be able to protect the parts of our jobs we love, and strengthen the benefits, pay, and job stability available to all workers. Together we can build an even better Sega. We hope our victory today is an inspiration to other workers across the gaming industry. Together, we can raise standards for all workers across the industry.”</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/sega-of-america-workers-overwhelmingly-vote-to-unionize-192839100.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/sega-of-america-workers-overwhelmingly-vote-to-unionize-192839100.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e7a0b6de-8855-4ff5-b082-dfc5928e81c5</guid><dc:creator> Kris Holt</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jul 2023 19:28:39 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689017320</ingested><modified> 2023-07-10T19:28:43+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Unions]]></category><category><![CDATA[Labor Issues]]></category><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3335" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-11/853ce330-672e-11ed-b7fc-a3f173ec499e" width="5000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3335" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-11/853ce330-672e-11ed-b7fc-a3f173ec499e" width="5000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[CHIBA, JAPAN - 2022/09/17: Sonic the Hedgehog balloon at the Sega exhibition area at Tokyo Game Show 2022. After a two years break forced by the Covid-19 pandemic, the Tokyo Game Show returned to Makuhari Messe in Chiba, Japan. (Photo by Stanislav Kogiku/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sonic the Hedgehog balloon at the Sega exhibition area at...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Massachusetts weighs outright ban on selling user location data]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> The Massachusetts state legislature is considering a bill that would ban the sale of users&#39; phone location data. If passed, the Location Shield Act would be the first such law in the nation as Congress stalls on comprehensive user privacy solutions on a national scale. The state&#39;s proposed legislation would also require a warrant for law enforcement to access user location data from data brokers.</p><p> Today, <em>The Wall Street Journal</em> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Wall Street Journal;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2f007401-3eaa-4237-b69b-54ccbe125502&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Wall+Street+Journal&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASaoHdtUi1e5Ij0Iw8Pv2M6Fbg_PDdGyPFiIHaj2JA51&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ffirst-u-s-ban-on-sale-of-cellphone-location-data-might-be-coming-fbe47e53" class="rapid-with-clickid">published a report</a> with numerous details on the proposed legislation, following earlier discussions at the state house (as <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.atholdailynews.com/Lawmakers-hear-plea-for-location-shield-law-51479799">reported by</a> <em>The Athol Daily News</em> ). Of course, the bill wouldn&#39;t prevent Massachusetts residents from using their phone&#39;s location services for things that directly benefit them — like Google Maps navigation, DoorDash deliveries or hailing an Uber. However, it would bar tech companies and data vendors from selling that data to third parties — a practice without any clear consumer benefit.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> The Location Shield Act is <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.aclum.org/en/ban-sale-location-data">backed by the ACLU</a> and various <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.progressivemass.com/location-shield-testimony-2023/">progressive and pro-choice groups</a> , who see a greater urgency to block the dissemination of user location in a post-Dobbs world. As red states increasingly criminalize abortion, <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/data-privacy-period-tracking-apps-130054404.html">concerns have grown</a> over the transfer of user data to catch women traveling out of state to undergo the procedure or access medication. In addition, the bill&#39;s backers raise concerns about national security and digital-stalking implications.</p><p> Opposing the legislation is the State Privacy &amp; Security Coalition, a trade association representing the tech industry. “The definition of sale is extremely broad,” said Andrew Kingman, an association lawyer. He says the group supports heightened protections but would prefer giving consumers “the ability to opt-out of sale,” as other state laws have done, rather than imposing an outright ban. Of course, making it optional rather than a complete ban would likely be much better for data brokers&#39; bottom lines.</p><p> Requiring law enforcement to provide a warrant to access user location data could also help curtail the <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-07-federal-agencies-buy-location-data-track-immigrants.html">rising trend</a> of law enforcement <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/secret-service-bought-location-data-locate-x-165531624.html">buying that information</a> commercially. A 2022 ACLU investigation found that the Department of Homeland Security <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/homeland-security-bulk-phone-location-data-aclu-153647669.html">bought over 336,000 data points</a> to essentially bypass the Fourth Amendment requirement for a search warrant. Although the US Supreme Court has said a warrant is usually needed for agencies to access location data from carriers, purchasing the data from private companies has served as a loophole.</p><p> The Massachusetts legislative session runs through next year, and the bill&#39;s backers show optimism that it will pass. “I have every reason to be optimistic that something will be happening in this session,” MA Senate Majority Leader Cindy Creem (D), the bill&#39;s sponsor, told the <em>WSJ</em> .</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/massachusetts-weighs-outright-ban-on-selling-user-location-data-191637974.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/massachusetts-weighs-outright-ban-on-selling-user-location-data-191637974.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 2a37112d-83ef-4f2f-be78-f96939d1bda0</guid><dc:creator> Will Shanklin</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jul 2023 19:16:37 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689016624</ingested><modified> 2023-07-10T19:17:07+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="3565" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2020-02/ee8133c0-5726-11ea-bfff-54b8ef6d7aa8" width="5315"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3565" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-images/2020-02/ee8133c0-5726-11ea-bfff-54b8ef6d7aa8" width="5315"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Future Publishing via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[LONDON, UNITED KINGDOM - JUNE 4: Detail of a man holding up an Honor 20 Pro smartphone with the Uber transport app visible on screen, while taxis queue in the background, on June 4, 2019. (Photo by Olly Curtis/Future via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Smartphone And Apps On Location]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hulu debuts hub for adult animation and anime]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Animation is big business for Hulu, as the streamer&#39;s roster of cartoons regularly rank in the top ten for hours watched on the platform, thanks to shows like <em>Bob&#39;s Burgers, Futurama, King of the Hill</em> and many more. Seeking to capitalize on the popularity of adult animation, Hulu&#39;s launching a sub-brand to house all of its animated and anime-based content, <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/hulu-animayhem-adult-animation-anime-1235664184/"><ins>as originally reported by</ins> <em><ins>Variety.</ins></em></a> Animayhem <em>&nbsp;</em> is now the home for legacy content like the above titles and original content like <em>Solar Opposites</em> and <em>Koala Man.</em></p><p> All told, the hub/sub-brand allows access to 2,600 episodes of traditional animated programming, spread across 46 series, and a whopping 18,400 episodes of anime, spread across 435 series. That&#39;s over 20,000 episodes of cartoon goodness, for those keeping count. As such, Hulu is advertising the platform as the streamer&#39;s “Animation Destination.” </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="ead64e96185a4eeaa85523246fbbbd31"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SkEfbi7M6Bo" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p> The surprise-launch of Animayhem comes just two weeks <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/futurama-returns-july-24th-as-a-hulu-original-after-a-10-year-hiatus-203316031.html"><ins>before the latest</ins> <em><ins>Futurama</ins></em> <ins>reboot,</ins></a> and that&#39;s just the start of the streamer&#39;s plans for animation domination. Hulu&#39;s ordered new episodes of Mike Judge&#39;s <em>King of the Hill</em> and it plans on having a heavy presence at this year&#39;s San Diego Comic-Con, promising an immersive experience called “Hulu Animayhem: Into the Second Dimension.”</p><p> In the meantime, the hub&#39;s already available as part of the standard Hulu subscription, so go ahead and binge <em>Archer, Family Guy</em> and all the hundreds upon hundreds of available anime series like <em>One Piece</em> and <em>Naruto.</em></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/hulu-debuts-hub-for-adult-animation-and-anime-182929897.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/hulu-debuts-hub-for-adult-animation-and-anime-182929897.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 467cb4fb-d72b-484e-8ef9-a46aefa88993</guid><dc:creator> Lawrence Bonk</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jul 2023 18:29:29 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689013770</ingested><modified> 2023-07-10T18:29:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Visual Arts]]></category><category><![CDATA[Humanities]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cartoons & Comics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Animation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/932619a0-1f4b-11ee-beef-aad57ef2fb58" width="2032"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:m